properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 20 at 9:07AM AKST until February 21 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blowing snow occurring. Visibilities one half mile or
less at times in blowing snow. Additional snow accumulations of
up to 3 inches.

* WHERE...Along the coast and Nunivak Island.

* WHEN...Until noon AKST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on reduced visibilities in blowing snow. The
dangerously cold wind chills as low as 35 below zero could cause
frostbite on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction: Slow down and use caution while traveling.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST FRIDAY FOR THE COAST AND NUNIVAK ISLAND... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY IS CANCELLED
